# Documentation Common Mistakes

## Code Mistakes

### SQL Reserved Words as Identifiers
- WRONG: `SELECT name, date FROM users;` (date is reserved)
- CORRECT: Use backticks or choose different names

### Unescaped Special Characters
- WRONG: Strings with single quotes not escaped
- CORRECT: Use `\'` or set proper escaping

## Link Mistakes

### Relative Paths
- WRONG: `../mysql/sql/basic/overview`
- CORRECT: `/mysql/sql/basic/overview`

### Directory Without Index
- WRONG: `/mysql`
- CORRECT: `/mysql/index`

## Formatting Mistakes

### Code Blocks Without Language
- WRONG: ``` SELECT * FROM users ```
- CORRECT: ```sql SELECT * FROM users ```

### Title Separator Without Content
- WRONG: # Title then --- then ## Title2
- CORRECT: # Title content ## Title2

## Checklist
- [ ] SQL syntax is correct
- [ ] Links use absolute paths
- [ ] Code blocks have language tags (sql, bash, etc.)
- [ ] Run npm run build to verify
